negotiations, that's great.

13:32.311 --> 13:36.081 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I liked what he said yesterday
better than
what he said today.

13:36.182 --> 13:37.249 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Why?

13:37.349 --> 13:39.585 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN MERRILL: For the reasons
that you mentioned.

13:39.685 --> 13:45.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Because he said
-- it sounded
more clear that he was open to
direct...

13:45.157 --> 13:46.058 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JOHN MERRILL: Yes, exactly.

13:46.158 --> 13:47.059 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: To direct talks.

13:47.159 --> 13:48.994 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What about this?

13:49.094 --> 13:51.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BALBINA HWANG: I think this
whole debate about
engagement, not engagement, is
it right or

13:51.897 --> 13:56.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wrong, do we need preconditions
