14:05.244 --> 14:07.780 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
First, negotiations take more
than one party.

14:07.880 --> 14:11.116 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Just as it takes two to tango,
it takes two
to negotiate.

14:11.217 --> 14:17.456 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And North Korea very
specifically denied every
overture by President Obama for
eight years

14:17.556 --> 14:20.392 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to enter into any kind of talks,
number one.

14:20.492 --> 14:24.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Number two, the six-party talks
were actually
very critical.

14:24.630 --> 14:30.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Ambassador Christopher Hill,
as you know,
who led the talks, his point was
that it established

14:30.436 --> 14:36.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
