defend the Christian

20:09.041 --> 20:13.212 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
community, such as putting armed
guards around
churches or the president making
statements

20:13.312 --> 20:17.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about how the government -- the
people should
-- there should be no
discrimination against

20:17.849 --> 20:22.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Copts and no violence against
Copts, it makes
it possible for Islamic radicals
to point

20:23.021 --> 20:27.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the government and say to
Egyptians, look
at these guys, they're on the
side of Christians,

20:27.159 --> 20:31.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they care more about Christians
than they
do about the average Muslim
Egyptian.

20:31.296 --> 20:34.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: So, is it part
of a larger
strategy for ISIS then in the
region?

20:34.967 --> 20:37.202 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TAREK MASOUD: It may be.

20:37.302 --> 20:42.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Clearly, everywhere that ISIS
operates, they
try to polarize societies,
foment sectarian

20:42.774 --> 20:44.509 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and religious dissension.

20:44.610 --> 20:49.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The other thing to note, though,
again that
the problem of violence and
discrimination

20:49.147 --> 20:55.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with Copts in Egypt far predates
ISIS and
far predates the government of
President Sisi.

20:55.354 --> 20:57.689 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it's not just a reflection
of ISIS strategy.

20:57.789 --> 21:00.425 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's a reflection of deep
dysfunctions in
Egyptian society.

21:00.525 --> 21:03.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Finally, I
want to ask about
this image that is circulating
today.

21:03.996 --> 21:08.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is of the pope embracing an
imam there
in Egypt.

21:08.700 --> 21:11.903 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It almost seems like there's a
