21:12.004 --> 21:16.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Will an image like that travel
as far and
as fast as some of these ISIS
videos make

21:16.174 --> 21:17.442 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it throughout the Muslim world?

21:17.542 --> 21:19.278 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TAREK MASOUD: One really hopes
so.

21:19.378 --> 21:24.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One thing that's really been
remarkable about
Pope Francis is that he really
isn't just

21:24.182 --> 21:26.118 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the pope of the world's
Catholics.

21:26.218 --> 21:31.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He really seems to be the pope
of all peoples,
and particularly the world's
downtrodden and

21:31.990 --> 21:33.725 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
disadvantaged.

21:33.825 --> 21:37.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think one thing that's
worth noting
is that, in his statement, the
pope called

21:37.729 --> 21:41.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the Egyptian government to do
more to respect
human rights.

21:41.667 --> 21:45.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he wasn't just talking about
the human
rights of Egypt's Christians,
